Connect and Sync Your Data to CRM Analytics

The Tableau Online connector syncs data sources embedded in a workbook from Tableau Online to CRM Analytics.

Connection Details
Before using this connector, assemble your data in Tableau Online.
Decide which tables to include. Table names must be alphanumeric, with no special characters, and start with a letter.
Publish an extract data source of your tables. Only extract data is supported.
Create a workbook including this data source.
Publish the workbook to a project.

The Tableau Online account used to create this connection must have at least Site Explorer role.

On the Data Manager Connections tab, click New Connection.
Click the name of the connector, and click Next.
Enter the connector settings:
Connection Name
Developer Name
Description
Server URL
Username (optional)
Content URL
Password (optional)

Authentication Type: Password or PersonalAccessToken
Personal Access Token Name (optional)
Personal Access Token Secret (optional)
Project Name
Workbook Name
Datasource Name
Schema Name

Keep these behaviors in mind when working with the Tableau Online connector:
Connected object names must start with a letter and contain only letters, digits, or underscores.
This connector can sync up to 100,000 rows or 500 MB per object.
This connector can only read data from a published workbook.
title: Connecting Salesforce CRM Analytics to Tableau Online
